class Solution {
public:
    int lastStoneWeight(vector<int>& stones) 
    {
        if(stones.size()==1) return stones[0];
        priority_queue<int> maxheap;
        for(auto& ele:stones)
        {
            maxheap.push(ele);
        }

        while(maxheap.size()>1)
        {
            int y=maxheap.top();maxheap.pop();
            int x=maxheap.top();maxheap.pop();

            if(y!=x)
            {
                maxheap.push(y-x);
            }
        }

        return maxheap.empty() ? 0 :maxheap.top();
    }
};

Time Complexity: O(n log n)

- Building the max-heap by inserting n stones takes O(n log n).
- In the worst case, we perform (n - 1) smash operations.
- Each smash involves:
    • 2 pop operations → O(log n)
    • 1 push operation (if needed) → O(log n)
- Therefore, total time = O(n log n).

Space Complexity: O(n)

- The max-heap stores at most n stones.
